Audit summary for Waves 3-8:
- Wave 3 Incidencias: mostly implemented in prior Wave 10 per docs/website-fix-log.md. I did not rework it.
- Wave 4 Recorridos: P1 gaps genuinely remained around role/plan ownership, conserje vs supervisor visibility, and active execution ambiguity.
- Wave 5 Mapa: P1 gaps remained around visible markers and map-click hallazgo context. Existing save path already carried map lat/lng into finding metadata, but route/issue visibility was still fragile.
- Wave 6 Inventario: P1 gaps remained around supervisor seeing count capture and lacking stockout/procurement actioning.
- Wave 7 Proyectos: P1 gaps remained around work assignment 400 risk, building context, and no existing item update path.
- Wave 8 Gerencia/Junta: several P1/P2 drill-down/reporting items remain. I only addressed the feasible schema-free Gerencia Plan Maestro ownership gap.

Implemented code changes:
- `aproviva-suite/js/modules/gemba.js`
  - Restricted Plan Maestro creation to `supervisor`; Gerencia keeps oversight only.
  - Added template/round owner metadata (`plan_role`, `plan_owner`) without schema changes.
  - Split fallback plans so conserje gets daily operational plans and supervisor gets weekly supervisor plans.
  - Conserje sees only conserje-owned rounds; supervisor sees supervisor-owned and team oversight rounds.
  - Active and next-action cards now show `Dueño` to reduce wrong-recorrido ambiguity.
  - Template form stores role/owner in metadata for future filtering.
- `aproviva-suite/js/modules/mapa.js`
  - Added route preview markers from GeoJSON when no saved route waypoints exist, so the map is not blank.
  - Preview markers are non-draggable and clearly labeled as base route references.
- `aproviva-suite/js/modules/inventario.js`
  - Hid `Registrar conteo` from supervisor.
  - Added supervisor `Actualizar reposición` workflow with item, status, OC reference, and required comment.
  - Moved long alert/catalog/movement sections below the action flow; catalog and movement sections collapse by default.
  - Procurement action persists as an `inventory_movements` adjustment with metadata, preserving previous balance to avoid null-balance writes.
- `aproviva-suite/js/modules/proyectos.js`
  - Added `building_id` to work assignment creation/import/backlog payloads.
  - Added update modal for existing work orders: status, priority, due date, and progress comment in metadata history.
  - Removed the prior `verified_at` update from the quick advance path to avoid schema-specific 400 risk.

